    "Sulaiman Al Habib is the founder and chairman of Riyadh-based hospital group Dr. Sulaiman Al Habib Medical Services Group, known as HMG.",
    "Al Habib, a trained pediatrician, founded the group in 1995 and took it public on the Saudi stock exchange in 2020; he owns a 40% stake.",
    "The group owns and runs hospitals and medical clinics in several cities in Saudi Arabia as well as in Dubai and Bahrain; it also operates a chain of pharmacies.",
    "In addition to traditional hospitals, the group has centers specialized in fertility, dermatology, plastic surgery, obesity treatment and more.",
    "In the late 1980s, Al Habib served as the head of the pediatrics department at the Security Forces Hospital in Riyadh."
